# Mokumo database topology
#
# Multi-tenant SQLite layout: kikan owns meta.db (platform);
# each profile gets its own application DB whose filename comes from Graft::db_filename().
#
# Render: d2 docs/diagrams/db-topology.d2 docs/diagrams/db-topology.svg

direction: down

title: |md
  # Database topology
  Kikan owns platform-wide state. Each profile gets its own application DB. Backup snapshots both.
| {near: top-center}

mokumo_data_dir: ~/Library/Application Support/com.breezybayslabs.mokumo/\n(macOS — equivalent on Linux/Windows) {
  style: {fill: "#f1f5f9"; stroke: "#475569"}

  meta_group: Platform (kikan-owned) {
    style: {fill: "#dcfce7"; stroke: "#166534"}
    meta: meta.db {
      shape: cylinder
      style: {fill: "#f0fdf4"; stroke: "#16a34a"; bold: true}
    }
    meta_tables: |md
      **`meta.db`** (platform-wide)

      - `users` — admin + employee accounts
      - `sessions` — tower-sessions
      - `profiles` — registry of all profiles
      - `profile_active_extensions` — per-profile extension activation
      - `schema_version` — kikan-owned migration ledger
      - `activity_log` — platform-wide audit
    |
    session: session.db\n(tower-sessions ephemeral) {
      shape: cylinder
      style: {fill: "#f0fdf4"; stroke: "#16a34a"}
    }
  }

  profile_group: Per-profile (vertical-owned via Graft::db_filename) {
    style: {fill: "#dbeafe"; stroke: "#1e40af"}
    demo: profiles/demo/mokumo.db {
      shape: cylinder
      style: {fill: "#eff6ff"; stroke: "#2563eb"}
    }
    production: profiles/production/mokumo.db {
      shape: cylinder
      style: {fill: "#eff6ff"; stroke: "#2563eb"}
    }
    profile_tables: |md
      **Per-profile `mokumo.db`** (vertical)

      - `customers`, `shops`, `quotes`, `invoices`
      - `kanban_columns`, `cards`
      - `products`, `inventory`, `pricing`
      - `sequences` (numbering)
      - vertical migrations contributed by `MokumoApp: Graft`
      - extension side tables (post-Wave-8)
    |
  }

  recovery: Recovery & backup {
    style: {fill: "#fef3c7"; stroke: "#92400e"}
    pin_dir: "profiles/<id>/recovery/\n(PIN-drop dir; path from Graft::recovery_dir())" {
      shape: page
      style: {fill: "#fffbeb"; stroke: "#d97706"}
    }
    backups: backups/\n(VACUUM INTO snapshots, kikan-managed) {
      shape: page
      style: {fill: "#fffbeb"; stroke: "#d97706"}
    }
  }
}

backup_flow: Backup-before-migrate flow (Wave 1) {
  style: {fill: "#fce7f3"; stroke: "#9f1239"}
  step1: 1. Detect schema mismatch on Engine::boot {style.fill: "#fdf2f8"; style.stroke: "#be185d"}
  step2: 2. VACUUM INTO meta.db.bak-vX.Y.Z {style.fill: "#fdf2f8"; style.stroke: "#be185d"}
  step3: 3. VACUUM INTO active mokumo.db.bak-vX.Y.Z {style.fill: "#fdf2f8"; style.stroke: "#be185d"}
  step4: 4. Apply migration DAG (transactional) {style.fill: "#fdf2f8"; style.stroke: "#be185d"}
  step5: 5. Verify integrity ➜ commit; on fail ➜ refuse-to-downgrade error {style.fill: "#fdf2f8"; style.stroke: "#be185d"}
  step1 -> step2 -> step3 -> step4 -> step5
}

mokumo_data_dir.profile_group.demo -> mokumo_data_dir.recovery.backups: snapshot {style.stroke: "#9f1239"; style.stroke-dash: 3}
mokumo_data_dir.profile_group.production -> mokumo_data_dir.recovery.backups: snapshot {style.stroke: "#9f1239"; style.stroke-dash: 3}
mokumo_data_dir.meta_group.meta -> mokumo_data_dir.recovery.backups: snapshot {style.stroke: "#9f1239"; style.stroke-dash: 3}

notes: |md
  ## Why this shape

  - **Kikan owns `meta.db`** (platform state) — every app on kikan gets the same shape.
  - **Per-profile app DB** filename comes from `Graft::db_filename()` (Mokumo returns `"mokumo.db"`). Another vertical on kikan picks its own filename without modifying kikan.
  - **`tower-sessions`** stays in its own ephemeral `session.db` so login/logout doesn't touch the platform or vertical DBs.
  - **Backup scope** = `meta.db` + active per-profile DB. Both written via `VACUUM INTO` (consistent snapshot, no WAL/SHM coordination needed).
  - **PIN recovery dir** is app-supplied via `Graft::recovery_dir(profile_id)`; kikan watches & validates, app picks the location.
| {near: bottom-center}
